{"id":76626,"title":"Prevalence of metabolic syndrome in Chinese nickel-exposed workers.","abstract":"The prevalence of metabolic syndrome (MS) was investigated in Chinese nickel-exposed workers. A total of 35 104 subjects were enrolled in this study. The age-adjusted prevalence of MS, BMI?25, diabetes, hypertension, and abnormal lipid was 13.9%, 29.5%, 12.8%, 27.5%, and 47.1%, respectively. The prevalence of BMI?25, hyperglycemia, and hypertension increased with the age of males and females, and was higher in males than in females (37.1% vs 21.5%, 15.9% vs 12.1%, 35.0% vs 24.3%, 54.3% vs 40.4%). ","date":"2014-06-25","categories":"Nutritional and Metabolic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24961859","annotations":[{"name":"Diabetes mellitus","weight":0.834159,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetes_mellitus"},{"name":"Hypertension","weight":0.819013,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypertension"},{"name":"China","weight":0.496625,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China"},{"name":"Metabolism","weight":0.460335,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metabolism"},{"name":"Metabolic syndrome","weight":0.401208,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metabolic_syndrome"},{"name":"Hyperglycemia","weight":0.268791,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyperglycemia"},{"name":"Lipid","weight":0.188661,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lipid"},{"name":"Body mass index","weight":0.100679,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Body_mass_index"},{"name":"Syndrome","weight":0.0604488,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syndrome"},{"name":"Prevalence","weight":0.0494293,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prevalence"},{"name":"Multiple sclerosis","weight":0.0203944,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiple_sclerosis"},{"name":"24 (TV series)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en